Action Guide for Girls' Education
http://www.igc.org/beijing/ngo/girls.html
The Action Guide for Girls' Education guide was created in response to the 1995 International Women's Conference in Beijing by the San Francisco Bay Area Girls' Education Network.
The network is comprised of a volunteer group of teachers, parents, writers, sociologists, and academicians who "wish to provide educators with concrete ways to raise awareness with regards to educational access and equity for girls around the globe."
Convention on the Rights of the Child
http://www.unicef.org/crc/
The United Nations Convention on the Rights of the Child is the most widely ratified human rights treaty in history.
Work on its drafting began in 1979 -- the International Year of the Child -- and was unanimously adopted by the United Nations General Assembly in 1989.
The Convention entered into force in September 1990.
